	abstract = {Abstract
            
              As climate change accelerates, extreme weather events become more severe and frequent. We analyzed the datasets of decade‐long observation (2005–2020) of mercury (Hg) stored in two subtropical evergreen forests to understand the impacts of extreme weather on the sequestration of atmospheric Hg in forest ecosystems. Results show a weak correlation between litterfall Hg and atmospheric Hg
              0
